text: Buying a 5 minute hourglass and taking it to the gym to flip between my sets and time my rest periods with

Quite unexpected that the only place in the modern world where you can find a hourglass being practically used are saunas. It's an object with rich symbolism, but a sauna is not where you would normally meditate on the passage of time, inevitability of death, yearly seasons, etc.
We need a second modern practical use of hourglasses location that is not sauna-related.

Stuff like this or the CocaCola formula is so alluring because it represents people seizing the mystery of marketing for themselves. Advertising offers happiness in the form of consumer goods you can't obtain on your own, learning trade secrets is like entering the holy of holies

Advertising offers a dreamlike reality of happiness and its mystery relies on corporate trade secrets and secret formulas. Once you know them, it's as if you become the magician yourself, you regain control over your destiny and are your own master now. You create your happiness.
